Review_Title: Doesn’t print on A4 photo paper
Review_Content: This printer arrived when expected and looks good. It took me a long time to set it up and connect to WiFi etc. (compared to my previous HP printer).I didn’t find the app as easy to use in myiPhone  as the HP and it didn’t have as many options for printing. The ink cartridges cost as much as the printer! I printed off A4 documents ok, but next time I can to use the printer it was off line and I couldn’t get it to reconnect. Eventually, I contacted Canon and their on line technical person got me trying various combinations of buttons and instructions and finally it was reconnected. I printed off 50 5 x 7 photos ok, but had to find a resizing app on line to get my photos to fit the paper.When I came to print an A4 photo of one of my paintings I spent hours trying to print it. I put new ink cartridges in, but kept getting an error code. I looked up the error code and it meant my settings were wrong. I checked and rechecked my settings, but they were fine. After much frustration I got onto the online technical advisor at Cannon who after a few minutes told me that my printer simply didn’t print A4 photos!! I was most annoyed and disappointed. I immediately looked to buy an HP printer. I checked before purchasing by speaking to someone at HP that it did print A4 photos and it does, so I am  awaiting its arrival. I am selling the 2 month old cannon with new cartridges for half price to my friend who just wants to print documents.

Review_Title: A fantastic printer for home use.
Review_Content: HP DeskJet 4220e All-in-One Printer.This device is not just a printer, it is a complete solution for our printing, scanning and copying needs. It has a maximum print speed of up to 20 ppm in black and white and 16 ppm in color, it is a very efficient machine without sacrificing print quality. In addition, the possibility of manually printing double-sided and access via dual-band Wi-Fi and USB 2.0 add versatility. It also includes the Instant Ink function, which is a printing service with which you receive the cartridges at home when you need them and it also takes care of their recycling, paying a monthly fee, of course. This function may be interesting for some people, but I prefer not to use it, I like to buy the ink only when I need it and, furthermore, with this monthly fee you will pay every month, whether you print or not. This HP DeskJet 4220e multifunction printer is a bet safe to use in our home, it is very versatile, the printing quality is very good and both the printer and the ink cartridges have a very low price. We have been using it at home for some time and we are delighted with it.

Review_Content: The HP DeskJet 2820e multifunction printer emerges as a stylish and practical solution for everyday printing needs, both in homes and small offices. Your 3-month Instant Ink printing promotion with HP+ adds considerable value, simplifying supplies management and offering convenience. One of the most notable features of the HP DeskJet 2820e is its multifunctionality. Not only does it print with remarkable quality, it also scans and copies effectively, making it a versatile tool for a variety of tasks. Its compact design is ideal for tight spaces, keeping a work area tidy and free of clutter. The HP Instant Ink service is a big draw, especially for those who print regularly. This system monitors your ink levels and automatically ships new cartridges before you run out. The first 3 months free is a great way to try out the service and see how it can make your life easier, eliminating the need to remember to buy ink. The DeskJet 2820e's print quality is impressive for a printer in its price range. Text documents print clearly and accurately, while photos and graphics come out with vivid colors and sharp details. This quality, combined with the automatic double-sided printing capability, makes it efficient and economical in terms of paper consumption. Connectivity is another strong point. With Wi-Fi connection options, you can easily print from multiple devices, including smartphones and tablets, adding convenience and flexibility to your workflow. However, there are aspects that could be improved. The print speed is not the fastest on the market, which could be a drawback for those who need to print large volumes of documents quickly. Additionally, the HP Instant Ink service requires a subscription after the first 3 months free, which involves a recurring expense. Personally, I find the HP DeskJet 2820e to be a solid option for home users and small offices looking for a reliable and multifunction printer. economical. It offers excellent print quality, ease of use, and convenient ink service, although it's important to consider print speed and long-term subscription costs.

Su promoción de 3 meses de impresión Instant Ink con HP+ añade un valor considerable, simplificando la gestión de consumibles y ofreciendo comodidad.Una de las características más destacadas de la HP DeskJet 2820e es su multifuncionalidad. No solo imprime con una calidad notable, sino que también escanea y copia con eficacia, lo que la convierte en una herramienta versátil para una variedad de tareas. Su diseño compacto es ideal para espacios reducidos, manteniendo un área de trabajo ordenada y libre de desorden.El servicio HP Instant Ink es un gran atractivo, especialmente para aquellos que imprimen regularmente. Este sistema monitorea tus niveles de tinta y envía automáticamente nuevos cartuchos antes de que te quedes sin ellos. Los primeros 3 meses gratuitos son una excelente manera de probar el servicio y ver cómo puede facilitar tu vida, eliminando la necesidad de recordar comprar tinta.La calidad de impresión de la DeskJet 2820e es impresionante para una impresora de su rango de precio. Los documentos de texto se imprimen con claridad y precisión, mientras que las fotos y gráficos salen con colores vivos y detalles nítidos. Esta calidad, combinada con la capacidad de impresión automática a doble cara, la hace eficiente y económica en términos de consumo de papel.La conectividad es otro punto fuerte. Con opciones de conexión Wi-Fi, puedes imprimir fácilmente desde varios dispositivos, incluyendo smartphones y tablets, lo que agrega comodidad y flexibilidad a tu flujo de trabajo.Sin embargo, hay aspectos que podrían mejorarse. Review_Content: This HP all-in-one printer is perfect for those looking to print, scan and copy with ease. You can print wirelessly thanks to Wi-Fi connectivity, which is great for printing directly from your mobile phone. It has an automatic document feeder that allows us to scan and copy multiple pages easily, saving time and effort. Use the HP Smart mobile app to print, scan, copy or even fax directly from your phone. It is quite easy to useThe printer has a Wi-Fi connection that automatically reconnects if it is lost, so don't worry about losing connection during an important print. If we want to send faxes, the smart software allows you to add files from your phone, scan with the printer's camera or scanner, and even save cover page templates. It uses original HP ink cartridges, with standard and high-capacity options I have not tested the compatible ones. We can scan documents in different formats such as JPEG, TIFF, PDF, BMP and PNG. Mobile Printing function, compatible with Apple AirPrint, Chrome OS and Mopria certification for easy printing from mobile devices. We have the HP Instant Ink Service to facilitate automatic ink replenishment when necessary and not have to worry about ink. It is an all-in-one printer that simplifies printing, scanning and copying. With its wireless connectivity, it is an excellent option for those looking for an easy-to-use printer in their day to day.

Review_Content: We are looking at a device that we can identify as an all-in-one, since we are not just looking at a printer, it can also scan and photocopy, in addition, it has a sheet feeder that offers a capacity of 35 pages, perhaps not much , but it will be enough for the most common tasks. Currently we can find many models presented by different brands, but we know that HP has recognized experience in this type of device. One of the most important aspects to take into account before purchasing a printer, in addition to having the support of a renowned manufacturer, will also be the cost of its consumables. In this aspect, laser printers are the ones that offer the best quantity-cost performance, but these devices are much more expensive, for this reason the option that this model offers us is interesting, I am referring to the possibility of being able to obtain laser cartridges. ink directly in the desired direction at very reasonable prices. This is a plan that we can choose depending on the use we make of the printer per month, for sporadic use, 10 sheets/month, the cost will be €1.49/month and if you need to print up to 50 sheets per month, the cost will be €4.99/month. Perhaps the most interesting plan for those who use the printer intensively is the one that costs 6.99/month, since it allows you to print up to a total of 100 pages per month. An aspect that I did not like , is the ink cartridge recognition system, that is, it will not work with cartridges that are not original. Personally, I think that this aspect should be the buyer's decision to decide whether or not they want to use the original consumables. I must point out that the paper output support did not seem very robust to me, probably with use it will end up getting damaged. Its initial configuration is simple, but we must bear in mind that for this we will need a mobile phone to follow the steps, it will even be necessary to access the menu configuration, since, on the screen of the printer itself, we will only obtain information from the status of the device and the ink level of its cartridges. The aspect that I liked the least is knowing that it is not compatible with automatic duplex mode, in this case, we will have to turn the sheet over manually when we want to print on both sides. In general, an economical, simple printer and without waiting it works very quickly. The main aspect to take into account, to determine if this model is the one you need, will be if you are interested in the prices of the plans that HP offers to receive the ink cartridges.

Orginal_Review: Estamos ante un dispositivo que podemos identificar como, un todo en uno, ya que no estamos tan solo ante una impresora, también puede escanear y fotocopiar, además, dispone de un alimentador de hojas que ofrece una capacidad de 35 folios, quizás no sea mucho, pero será suficiente para las tareas más habituales.Actualmente podemos encontrar muchos modelos presentados por diferentes marcas, pero sabemos que HP, tiene una reconocida experiencia en este tipo de dispositivos. Uno de los aspectos más importantes a tener en cuenta antes de adquirir una impresora, además de tenga el apoyo de un reconocido fabricante, será también el coste de sus consumibles. En este aspecto, las impresoras láser son las que ofrecen el mejor rendimiento cantidad-coste, pero estos dispositivos son mucho más costosos, por este motivo resulta interesante la opción que nos ofrece este modelo, me refiero a la posibilidad de poder obtener los cartuchos de tinta directamente en la dirección deseada a unos precios muy ajustados. Se trata de un plan que podremos escoger dependiendo del uso que le hagamos a la impresora al mes, para un uso esporádico, 10 hojas / mes, el coste será de 1,49€/mes y en caso de necesitar imprimir hasta 50 hojas por mes, el coste será de 4,99€/mes. Quizás el plan más interesante para aquellos que le den un uso intensivo a la impresora, es el que tiene un coste de 6,99/mes, ya que permite imprimir hasta un total de 100 páginas por mes.Un aspecto que no me ha gustado, es el sistema de reconocimiento de los cartuchos de tinta, es decir, no funcionará con aquellos cartuchos que no sean originales, personalmente, creo que este aspecto tendría que ser decisión del comprador quien decida si desea utilizar o no los consumibles originales. Review_Title: Very good print quality and easy to use
Review_Content: First of all, I say that at home we use the printer a lot, especially my daughter who is at university, and I have to say that this model perfectly meets all the necessary requirements for her daily life. It is a multifunction printer of the HP brand and specifically the DeskJet 4220e model, which is one of the newest of the brand. The printer has the ability to print, scan and copy, which makes it very versatile, since we can perform all these tasks without having to have additional devices. One of the features that we liked the most is that it has an automatic document feeder, so we can load a good batch of pages into the printer, and it will take them one by one to scan or copy them automatically, which is very comfortable. Another very notable aspect is that it has WIFI connectivity, so we can print documents directly from any mobile device or tablet without the need for cables (I have used it with Android and iOS), this feature is very convenient, so we do not have to have the printer. connected to a computer and depend on it to print. Regarding the print quality I have to admit that it is really good, it is a fast printer and when we use it with photographic paper the result is spectacular, I have used several brands of printers and I have to admit that HP is one of those that offer the highest quality. Regarding blacks, it offers a resolution of up to 1200 x 1200 dpi and with color, the resolution reaches up to 4800 x 1200 dpi, and when printing it makes almost no noise, which is especially appreciated if you print jobs at night. On the other hand, this HP printer offers what they call the “Instant Ink” service, with this service we can receive the ink directly at home before running out of it, since the printer detects that we have little ink left and sends the request automatically to HP. This service, in addition to being very convenient, is much more economical than having to buy the cartridges on our own, which honestly costs a lot. To know the service, the printer comes with 3 free months of service, which is phenomenal, we can choose the highest printing option during those 3 months and then change it to the one that suits our needs, according to our printing pace.

Orginal_Review: En primer lugar decir que en casa usamos la impresora bastante, sobre todo mi hija que está en la universidad, y tengo que decir que este modelo cumple perfectamente con todos los requisitos necesarios para su día a día.Se trata de una Impresora multifunción de la marca HP y en concreto el modelo DeskJet 4220e, que es de los más nuevos de la marca.La impresora tiene la capacidad de imprimir, escanear y copiar, lo que la hace muy versátil, ya que podemos realizar todas estas tareas sin necesidad de tener dispositivos adicionales. Una de las características que más nos han gustado es que dispone de un alimentador automático de documentos, por lo que podemos cargar un buen lote de folios en la impresora, y ésta los irá cogiendo uno a uno para escanearlos o copiarlos automáticamente, lo cual es muy cómodo. Otro aspecto muy destacable es que dispone de conectividad WIFI, por lo que podemos imprimir documentos directamente desde cualquier dispositivo móvil o tablet sin necesidad de cables (la he usado con Android e iOS), esta característica es comodísima, así no tenemos que tener la impresora conectada a un ordenador y depender de él para imprimir.Respecto a la calidad de impresión tengo que admitir que es realmente buena, es una impresora rápida y cuando la usamos con papel fotográfico el resultado es espectacular, he usado varias marcas de impresoras y tengo que admitir que HP es de las que más calidad ofrecen. Respecto a los negros, ofrece una resolución de hasta 1200 x 1200 ppp y con color, la resolución alcanza hasta 4800 x 1200 dpi, además a la hora de imprimir casi no hace ruido, lo cual se agradece sobre todo si imprimes trabajos por la noche.Por otro lado, esta impresora HP ofrece lo que llaman el servicio “Instant Ink”, con este servicio podemos recibir la tinta directamente en casa antes de quedarnos sin ella, ya que la impresora detecta que nos queda poca tinta y envía la petición automáticamente a HP. Este servicio además de ser muy cómodo es bastante más económico que teniendo que comprar los cartuchos por nuestra cuenta, que la verdad salen por un pico. Para conocer el servicio, la impresora viene con 3 meses gratuitos del mismo, lo cual está fenomenal, podemos elegir la opción de impresión más alta durante esos 3 meses y luego cambiarla a la que se adapte a nuestras necesidades, según nuestro ritmo de impresión.

Review_Title: A practical solution with advantages and disadvantages.
Review_Content: I tested the printer for a few days, and I have to say that I really liked it. The installation was very simple, I just had to follow the instructions on the screen and the HP Smart App, which guided me step by step. The printer connected quickly to my Wi-Fi network and my phone, and I was able to start printing right away. The print quality is very good, both in black and white and color, and the texts and images look sharp and with vivid colors. The print speed is also quite good, and I haven't noticed any jamming or misfeeds. The scan and copy function also works very well, and the automatic document feeder is very handy for scanning or copying documents from multiple pages. The scan quality is good, and you can adjust the size, format and resolution from the HP Smart App. The mobile fax function is also very useful, as it allows you to send scanned documents from your mobile to any fax number, without the need for a telephone line. The HP Smart App also allows you to print documents from the cloud, from email or from social networks, as well as monitor the ink level and the status of the printer. The printer has a compact and elegant design, and does not take up much space on the desk. The control panel is intuitive and easy to use, and has a 2.2-inch monochrome LCD screen that displays printer options and messages. The input tray has a capacity of 60 sheets, and the output tray has a capacity of 25 sheets, which is fine for home or small office use. The printer also has a silent mode, which reduces noise when printing, which is appreciated if you work in a quiet environment. Like any printer, it has its advantages and disadvantages: Advantages- It is a multifunction printer that can print, scan, copy and send by mobile fax in black and white and in color.- It has good print quality and speed, and allows for manual double-sided printing.- It has a 35-sheet automatic document feeder, which makes scanning and copying easy of multiple pages.- It has a dual-band Wi-Fi connection with automatic reset, Wi-Fi Direct, high-speed USB 2.0 and Apple AirPrint, which allow printing from different devices and sources.- It has the HP Smart App, which allows print, scan and manage the printer from your mobile or tablet.- You have the option of choosing HP+, which offers an additional year of warranty, three months of Instant Ink included and automatic ink delivery at home with the Instant Ink service. - It has a compact and elegant design, and an intuitive and easy-to-use control panel. - It has a silent mode, which reduces noise when printing. Disadvantages - Double-sided printing is manual, which means you have to press the - The LCD screen is monochrome and small, which can make it difficult to see some options or messages. - The capacity of the input and output trays is limited. , which may require frequent refills if you print a lot. - The HP+ option requires an HP account, a permanent Internet connection, and exclusive use of Original HP Ink for the life of the printer, which may limit the user's freedom of choice.

Review_Title: Very basic printer, printing is expensive.
Review_Content:
Media content could not be loaded.
                



The printer comes with a power cable, a black ink cartridge and a sample color ink cartridge, and various manuals and quick guides in several languages. It is a printer for home use, very basic and takes up considerable space on the desk. Getting started is simple, everything is done through the "HP Smart" application from a mobile phone or PC. The most convenient thing is to connect it using a Wi-Fi connection, the printer is only compatible with networks that are in the 2.4 Ghz band (this is a drawback, nowadays 5 Ghz networks are fully extended and are much faster) . Between the application and the printer, they tell you all the steps to complete the configuration. If you connect it via USB to a PC, the configuration is even simpler. As soon as you start it up, it gives the feeling (to me at least) that the printer is nothing more than an excuse to end up in a subscription service with HP for the supply of inks, with prices that are laughable. The most basic is a monthly printing of 10 pages for €0.99, wow! The most expensive, 300 pages per month for €24.99, if you exceed what you contracted, you know, you'll pay a premium. It's ridiculous. You have 2 months free (the third month are the cartridges that the printer already has), after verification of a valid payment method, once those two months have passed, you must pay until you cancel the subscription. We all know the policy that HP is following with compatible cartridges, however it warns you during the printer configuration that if you use those types of orange cartridges from China, they will be rejected through firmware updates, and that it works for you A cartridge today does not mean that it will continue to work for you tomorrow because the intention is to cover the use of these cartridges. With this message all my interest in the printer disappears. Logically you can ignore all those messages and buy the ink cartridges when you need them, if you buy the original ones, you have to assume that they have liquid gold inside, because they are not cheap (that's what they have change the head every time you change the cartridges). As for the operation of the printer, it is, as I said before, very basic, it scans, copies, prints, in black and white, in color, at an acceptable quality, but above all very slow. Using Wi-Fi, printing a 20-page document is a pain, it takes a long time to start printing, and it is most likely that there will be a printing failure halfway through (remember that it uses the 2.4 Ghz network). Using USB things improve a little, but not much, it is more stable when printing and faster when starting printing, but the speed does not improve. The same with scanning. I think there are better options on the market than this printer for home use, especially models just as capable as this one at a similar price with which you can use compatible cartridges. Although my recommendation is to go for models like the Ecotank, Megatank or similar, the printer is going to be more expensive, but over time you will save on ink. Note: If you are only going to print 10 sheets a month, it is better to go to a copy service and print them there, it is not worth buying any printer.

La impresora viene con un cable de alimentación, un cartucho de tinta negra y otro de color de muestra y diversos manuales y guías rápidas en varios idiomas.Es una impresora para uso doméstico, muy básica y que ocupa un espacio considerable en el escritorio. La puesta en marcha es sencilla, todo se hace al través de la aplicación "HP Smart" desde un móvil o desde un PC. Lo más cómodo es conectarla usando una conexión Wifi, la impresora sólo es compatible con redes que están en la banda de 2,4 Ghz (esto es un inconveniente, hoy en día las redes a 5 Ghz están totalmente extendidas y son bastante más rápidas). Entre la aplicación y la impresora te van diciendo todos los pasos para completar la configuración. Si la conectas por USB a un PC la configuración es más sencilla aún.Nada más la pones en marcha da la sensación (a mi por lo menos) de que la impresora no es más que una excusa para acabar en un servicio de suscripción con HP para el suministro de tintas, con unos precios que entra hasta risa. La más básica es una impresión mensual de 10 páginas por 0'99€, flipa! La más cara, 300 páginas al mes por 24'99€, si te excedes en lo contratado, ya sabes, a pagar un plus. Es ridículo. Tienes 2 meses gratis (el tercer mes son los cartuchos que ya lleva la impresora), previa verificación de un método de pago válido, una vez pasados esos dos meses, a pagar hasta que anulas la suscripción. Todos sabemos la política que está siguiendo HP con los cartuchos compatibles, no obstante te avisa durante la configuración de la impresora que de usar ese tipo de cartuchos naranjas de la china, que los van a ir rechazando mediante actualizaciones de firmware, y que te funcione un cartucho hoy no quiere decir que te siga funcionando mañana porque la intención que tienen es capar el uso de estos cartuchos. Con este mensaje todo mi interés por la impresora desaparece.Lógicamente puedes ignorar todos esos mensajes y comprar los cartuchos de tinta cuando los necesites, si los compras originales, tienes que suponer que dentro llevan oro líquido, porque no son baratos (es lo que tiene cambiar el cabezal cada vez que cambias los cartuchos).En cuanto al funcionamiento de la impresora, pues es como he dicho antes muy básica, escanea, copia, imprime, en blanco y negro, en color, a una calidad aceptable, pero sobre todo muy lenta. Por wifi imprimir un documento de 20 páginas es un dolor de muelas, tarda en empezar a imprimir una barbaridad, y lo más probable es que de un fallo de impresión a mitad (recordemos que va por la red de 2,4 Ghz). Por USB la cosa mejora un poco, pero tampoco mucho, es más estable a la hora de imprimir y más rápida en iniciar la impresión, pero la velocidad no mejora. Lo mismo con el escaneo.Creo que hay mejores opciones en el mercado que esta impresora para el uso en el hogar, sobre todo modelos iguales de capaces que este a un precio similar con los que si puedes usar cartuchos compatibles. Aunque mi recomendación es irse a modelos como los Ecotank, Megatank o similares, la impresora va a ser más cara, pero con el tiempo te lo vas a ahorrar en tinta.Nota: Si sólo vas a imprimir 10 hojas al mes, sale mejor irte a un servicio de copistería e imprimirlas ahí, no merece la pena que te compres ninguna impresora.

Review_Title: Delighted with its operation, design, quality, price.
Review_Content: This time I am going to review the HP DeskJet 2820e printer. We are impressed and very happy with it, both for its discreet and elegant white design, quality of materials and finishes, print quality and its value for money. Highlights: - Easy installation in about 10 minutes using the QR code and following directions. The only but is that you have to configure each device individually.- Possibility of remote printing, which can be disabled.- Very good print quality, it does not leave horizontal lines or stains on paper.- The scanner also works correctly.- Two packs are included of cartridges, one in black and one in tricolor and you have the option of joining their program so that they periodically send cartridges to your home before the ones you have are sold out.- The price seems incredibly great and surprisingly economical.- Yes You are looking for a printer to have at home for specific things or jobs, it is phenomenal. I hope my opinion is useful to you.

Orginal_Review: Esta vez voy a revisar la impresora HP DeskJet 2820e.Estamos impresionados y muy contentos con ella, tanto por su diseño discreto y elegante en blanco, calidad de materiales y acabados, calidad de impresión y su relación calidad precio.A destacar:- Instalación fácil en unos 10 minutos usando el código QR y siguiendo indicaciones. El único pero es que hay que configurar cada dispositivo individualmente.- Posibilidad de impresión remota, que se puede deshabilitar.- Calidad de impresión muy buena, no deja líneas horizontales ni mancha papel.- El escáner tambein funciona correctamente.- Se incluyen dos pack de cartuchos, uno en negro y otro tricolor y se da la opción de unirte a su programa para que te envíen cartuchos periódicamente a casa antes de que se agoten los que tienes puestos.- El precio me parece increíblemente estupendo y sorprendentemente económico.- Si estás buscando una impresora para tener un casa para cosas o trabajos puntuales, está fenomenal.Espero que mi opinión os resulte útil.

Review_Title: What a way to complicate life!!!
Review_Content: We have received this HP printer that when it arrives for the 50 euros it costs you think that it is wonderful for only 50 bucks, so well presented, with that roll of inks at home for 3 months, that goes through Wi-Fi, that does not need of cables.... it's a wonder. Well, none of that, so I'll tell you my experience. The printer reminds me a lot of the one I've also had from HP for many years, which is a 1050 identical in design to this one, which It does the same thing as this one, printing, acting as a photocopier, and a scanner. It's not that it's wonderful at making photographic prints, but for what it cost me in its day, which is more or less the same as this one, I don't know what I could ask for more, apart from the fact that I don't need a photographic printer, and if I want Photos are taken at a copy shop with a higher quality printer. I only want it for the day-to-day battle, and for my children to draw some drawings to color, and with this my 1050 and this one that has arrived works well. Therefore, as a printer or scanner it works correctly for the price it has, Come on, I would say that they are 50 euros well spent. Now the bad thing.....1- The configuration is yes or yes by wifi, we go because the engineer on duty got it into his balls that it had to be like that, because He wanted it, and then he would complain that we gave him bad scores. Well, nothing, there's no point in doing it over Wi-Fi, since it's either done in a moment, like what happened to me with the computer, or it becomes gibberish like what happened to me with my daughter's laptop, or something complicated with my tablet. my son. I haven't even tried it with my cell phone. Apart from the fact that when you do it it is very unstable and misconfigured... a bummer. How difficult was it to put a cable to the USB and make it plug and play? How difficult was it to do this? As I said before, it is a copy of the HP 1050 and I have never had configuration problems, or anything like that. 2- The ink thing at home, very good, but NO, THANK YOU. That thing about giving my credit card, my data, and who knows what else they control me through the software, what happens, let's see if one day I print a photo of a naked girl and they send me to the moral police to home. Passed. Also, if you give them up and forget to unsubscribe, you will have a withdrawal of money in your bank account that you will wonder, and what is that about? well, about this. Well, as I said, a good printer at a good price but they have screwed up with those customer loyalty policies, and complicating life with so much modernity.

No es que sea una maravilla haciendo impresiones fotograficas, pero para lo que me costo en su dia, que es mas o menos lo mismo que esta, no s ele puede pedir mas, aparte de que yo no necesito una impresora fotográfica, y si quiero fotos, me las hacen en una copistería con una impresora de mas calidad. Yo solo la quiero para la batalla del dia a dia, y para mis hijos sacarse algún dibujito para colorear, y con esto mi 1050 y esta que me ha llegado va bien.Por tanto como impresora o scanner funciona correctamente para el precio que tiene, vamos yo diría que son 50 euros bien invertidos.Ahora lo malo.....1- La configuración es si o si por wifi, vamos porque al ingeniero de turno se le metió en los cojo nes que tenia que ser asi, porque a el le dio la gana, y luego se quejara que le demos malas puntuaciones. Pues  nada, que hacerlo por wifi tiene tela, ya que igual se hace en un momento, como me paso con el ordenador, o se convierte en un galimatias como me paso con el portátil de mi hija, o en algo complicadillo con la tablet de mi hijo. Con el móvil ni lo he intentado. Aparte de que cuando lo haces es muy inestable y se desconfigura.. un rollo.Tan difícil era poner un cable al usb y que fuera un plug and play? tan difícil tan difícil era hacer esto?. Como es he dicho antes es una copia de la hp 1050 y esta nuca nunca he tenido problemas de configuración, ni nada por el estilo.2- Lo de las tintas en casa, muy bien, pero NO, GRACIAS. Eso de dar mi tarjeta de crédito, mis datos, y vete a saber que cosas mas me controlan por el sofware como que paso, a ver si un día me imprimo una foto de una chica en pelotas y me mandan a la policía de la moral a casa. Paso. Ademas como los des y te olvides de darte de baja, en tu cuenta del banco te vendrá una retirada de dinero que te preguntaras,,, y eso de que es? pues de esto.Pues lo dicho, una buena impresora a un buen precio pero que la han cagad o con esas políticas de fidelización de clientela, y complicarse la vida con tanta modernidad.

Review_Title: A practical solution with advantages and disadvantages.
Review_Content: I've been testing the printer for a few days now, and I have to say that I'm quite pleased with it. Setup was very easy, just following the instructions on the screen and in the HP Smart App, which guided me step by step. The printer quickly connected to my Wi-Fi network and my mobile, and I was able to start printing straight away. Print quality is very good, both in black and white and colour, and text and images are crisp and vibrant. Print speed is also quite good, and I haven't noticed any jams or misfeeds. The scan and copy function also works very well, and the automatic document feeder is very handy for scanning or copying multi-page documents. Scan quality is good, and you can adjust the size, format and resolution from the HP Smart App. The mobile fax function is also very useful, as it allows you to send scanned documents from your mobile to any fax number, without needing a phone line. The HP Smart App also lets you print documents from the cloud, email, or social media, as well as monitor ink levels and printer status. The printer has a sleek, compact design that doesn't take up much desk space. The control panel is intuitive and easy to use, with a 2.2-inch monochrome LCD display that shows printer options and messages. The input tray has a capacity of 60 sheets, and the output tray has a capacity of 25 sheets, which is fine for home or small office use. The printer also has a quiet mode, which reduces noise when printing, which is appreciated if you work in a quiet environment. Like any printer, it has its advantages and disadvantages: Advantages- It is a multifunction printer that can print, scan, copy and send by mobile fax in black and white and in color.- It has a good print quality and speed, and allows manual double-sided printing.- It has a 35-sheet automatic document feeder, which makes it easy to scan and copy multiple pages.- It has a dual-band Wi-Fi connection with automatic reset, Wi-Fi Direct, high-speed USB 2.0 and Apple AirPrint, which allow printing from different devices and sources.- It has the HP Smart App, which allows you to print, scan and manage the printer from your mobile or tablet.- You have the option to choose HP +, which offers an additional year of warranty, three months of Instant Ink included and automatic ink delivery at home with the Instant Ink service.- It has a compact and elegant design, and an intuitive and easy-to-use control panel.- It has a quiet mode, that reduces noise when printing. Disadvantages- Double-sided printing is manual, meaning you have to turn the paper over and feed it back into the printer to print the other side.- The LCD screen is monochrome and small, which can make it difficult to see some options or messages.- The capacity of the input and output trays is limited, which may require frequent refilling of paper if you print a lot.- The HP+ option requires an HP account, a persistent Internet connection, and exclusive use of Original HP Ink for the life of the printer, which may limit the user's freedom of choice.

Review_Title: Think carefully about whether you are interested before signing up for Instant Ink
Review_Content: In my house we don't normally need to print many things, but I thought that a printer like this could save us trips to the stationery store to print odd things. But I honestly don't know if I was right. These types of printers are cheap, relatively easy to configure (this one is a bit tricky with Wi-Fi, but oh well) and to use. The printing for my taste is average, but perhaps because in my work I use much better printers. But the problem is the cartridges: - the ones that come with the printer are much smaller than normal, they give you 4 or 5 sheets and that's it - then you can use the 305 or 305XL (the XL costs about twice as much as the normal ones), or compatible ones if the printer recognizes them and you have never used the Instant Ink service. In any case, if you don't print at least once a week, get used to the idea that they are going to dry out. - If you sign up for the Instant Ink service, they will send you the cartridges when the ones you have are running out. The printer must always be connected to Wi-Fi. You get 3 months free and I guess one more if you sign up using any of the codes posted in other reviews. But to benefit from those 3 free months you have to subscribe within 7 days of configuring the printer (I don't understand this rush). Then you have several plans to choose from: 10 sheets for €0.99, 50 sheets for €3.99, etc. But oh, they just raised it to €1.49, €4.99, etc. In a normal month I don't print even 10 sheets; then the unprinted ones are accumulated for the following month up to a maximum of 30. But if the printer decides to play dumb and print the pages in half, they count as printed. And if you go beyond the printed sheets, you pay for another pack of 10 sheets the same as the subscription. And the day you unsubscribe, the cartridges stop working even if they are full; You have to buy others (original HP, of course) to continue printing. In short, it seems to me that the cartridges last a very short time (if you don't use them often they dry out) and they are expensive. And I don't like not being able to use compatible cartridges. I only see the Instant Ink service as reasonable if you usually print a more or less fixed number of sheets each month. For occasional users, I think that neither the service nor the printer is worth it (because the cartridges will dry out if you don't use them). In my case I have configured it but I have not signed up for Instant Ink. When I run out of cartridges I'll see if I give it to a family member who will use it more.

Review_Title: WIFI printing! In this case meaning its free .....of WIFI
Review_Content: First you have to down load the app to use this. Ok not a big deal but...Then you have to sign up and give your card details to get the 3 months free ink. Except its not the ink your getting but 50 pages of printing per month then when the ink runs out they send you more, for the great price of £2.99 p.m. just don't, I mean DON'T go over your 50 pages Your expected to leave the printer switched on and connected to your network all the time so they can just monitor things for you. No. Not at all data mining you. Honest Gov.Set up is easy. If by easy you mean enjoying spending hours trying to get the app to work then register then try get the printer connected to your network, then do the same thing for the rest of your devices. Oh yes the hours just fly by.The good old printer cable port is covered by tape to encourage you to use the wonderful WIFI.And wonderful it is. If you enjoy playing Wack A Mole with your connections. Iv had Fillings that had more reliable WIFI connection than this printer! On the second day I gave up and removed the port tape and went old school with the reliable printer cable. So is it worth opening up your network to HP so they can monitor, for your own good you understand, everything you do? (That is when it actually feels like connecting to your network, and then it may also remember about those odd pages you sent a day or so ago and gave up on then suddenly decide spit them out at you almost completed). Well if you want the 'Talky Toaster' of printers then maybe.Conclusion: If you are looking to invite HP into your home and add some excitement to your otherwise dull printing experience then yup this is the printer for you. But keep your old printer cable handy.

Review_Title: Good print quality, economical and with free ink
Review_Content: Here we have the HP Deskjet 2820e multifunction printer, which comes with 3 months of free printing (Instant Ink). It connects via 2.4G Wi-Fi (be careful, it does not support 5G). In my experience, it has the usual problems, that from time to time the Wi-Fi connection is lost, and you have to stop it and reconnect it. It is curious because being just 5 meters from the router, it suddenly loses the connection intermittently. However, I have always been able to print so far. The printing speed is not bad for the price of the printer (7.5ppm in black / 5ppm in color), and the quality is quite good for office applications. The tray supports up to 60 sheets, although I have held 40 (I don't know what thickness of paper I am using). The scanner, good, without problems. Aesthetically the printer is beautiful, and it makes very little noise (the quietest I have had so far). The truth is that for the price compared to the ink that HP gives you, the Printer is practically free, so it is totally recommended.
Aggregation_Flag: Diseño: NuevaNombre de estilo: Sin alimentador automático
Orginal_Review: Aquí tenemos la impresora multifunción HP Deskjet 2820e, que viene con 3 meses de impresión gratis (Instant Ink). Se conecta por wifi 2.4G (ojo, no admite el de 5). Bajo mi experiencia, tiene los problemas de siempre, que de vez en cuando se pierde la conexión wifi, y hay que pararla y volverla a conectar. Es curioso porque estando a escasos 5 metros del router, de repente pierde la conexión de forma intermitente. No obstante, siempre he podido imprimir hasta el momento.La velocidad de impresión no está mal por el precio de la impresora (7.5ppm en negro / 5ppm en color), y la calidad es bastante buena para ofimática. La bandeja admite hasta 60 hojas, aunque a mi me han cabido 40 (no sé qué grosor de papel estoy usando). El scanner, bien, sin problemas.Estéticamente la impresora es bonita, y hace muy poco ruido (la más silenciosa que he tenido hasta el momento).La verdad es que por el precio que tiene frente a la tinta que te regala HP, la impresora te sale prácticamente gratis, así que es totalmente recomendable.

The LCD screen is very poor, you depend on your smartphone or PC for print settings. These are very limited, you cannot zoom or crop the image or select the size of the folio. Just rotate the image or the type of paper. The worst thing is that I can't link the printer via Wi-Fi (it only supports 2.4G) from home to the smartphone app, it gives an error in the last step. I have to download the image or pdf and then connect to the Wi-Fi that the printer emits, with limited functions. The print quality is decent. In principle, it only accepts original cartridges, although the pack remains at €25, the color ink does not last at all. The 2008 HP Photosmart is much better. A disappointment

Review_Title: Good printer at a competitive price
Review_Content: I bought this printer to replace another similar DeskJet that I had bought years ago and it stopped working. The installation is simple but when you sign up for the HP+ Instant Ink service, after selecting the subscription plan, the delivery address and the payment method, it Opens a window in the browser with information that you must read. At the bottom are the terms of service and a button to select that you accept them before you can continue. That button is hidden (you see a line instead of the typical box to select), you have to click on the line to accept the conditions and be able to continue with the installation. I find the HP+ Instant Ink service interesting, let's see how it works . The printer comes with a 3-month trial, here is a code to get an additional 1 month (xspxfb).Otherwise, a reliable printer with good value for money.

En la parte de abajo están las condiciones del servicio y un botón para seleccionar que las aceptas antes de poder continuar. Ese botón está oculto (se ve una línea en vez de la típica caja para seleccionar), tienes que clicar en la línea para aceptar las condiciones y poder continuar con la instalación.Me parece interesante el servicio HP+ Instant Ink, a ver qué tal funciona. Review_Content: To begin with, I confirm what has sometimes been noted, the printer is delivered without a protective cardboard which is not very discreet, however I do not know if it is systematic. I needed a printer affordable multifunction mainly for printing administrative documents and mainly black and white text. So I won't be able to give you my opinion on how it looks on photo paper. But the information that I was able to glean here and there says that the printer is quite hungry for ink, so I think that it should be reserved for occasional use rather than for intensive use.User of Apple devices , I had a lot of concerns about compatibility with the majority of this type of printer (and even more expensive printers). The reasons for my concerns were related to Apple's latest updates: MacOS Sonoma and iOS 17. Users reported issues with the scanning function no longer working after the system upgrade, and quite a few other problems that I will not list all. As far as I am concerned, after a really easy configuration with the HP Smart application (and not with a USB cable, which is not included in the package even if the The printer does have a USB port), all functions are operational. Other users had less luck with this configuration, while others, like me, did not encounter any problems at this stage, which precisely because of these negative comments, was the one I feared the most.L The printer is AirPrint compatible, which I think is the first thing to check before making your purchase if you have a Mac, iPhone or iPad. Many printers of all brands integrate this technology developed by Apple to print documents, without having to download or install drivers, but there may be exceptions. In the case of this printer it was still necessary to install HP Smart to do the basic configuration, which allows the brand to offer paid services in the process (this explains why the USB cable is only functional after having installed everything via Wi-Fi). After this configuration you can absolutely use the native applications of your Apple devices which all use AirPrint, whether for scanning or printing. This is a very subjective opinion, but I find the printer rather sober and pretty. As for the manufacturing quality at this price, you shouldn't expect solid gold, in fact the first thing I noticed, since it's almost the first thing to do, is that there is play at the power plug when you plug in the cord. Another rather annoying feature is that the printer is still quite noisy.
Aggregation_Flag: Diseño: NuevaNombre de estilo: Sin alimentador automático
Orginal_Review: Pour commencer je confirme ce qui a parfois été relevé, l'imprimante est bien livrée sans carton de protection ce qui n'est pas très discret, en revanche je ne sais pas si c’est systématique.J’avais besoin d’une imprimante multifonctions abordable essentiellement pour imprimer des documents administratifs et principalement du texte en noir et blanc. Je ne pourrai donc pas vous donner mon avis sur son rendu sur du papier photo. Mais les informations que j’ai pu glaner ça et là, disent que l’imprimante est assez gourmande en encre, donc je pense qu’elle serait plutôt à réserver pour un usage occasionnel plutôt que pour un usage intensif.Utilisateur d’appareils Apple, j’ai eu beaucoup d’inquiétudes concernant la compatibilité avec la majorité de ce type d’imprimante (et même avec des imprimantes plus coûteuses). Les raisons de mes inquiétudes étaient liées aux toutes dernières mises à jour d’Apple : MacOS Sonoma et iOS 17.  Les utilisateurs ont relevé des soucis avec la fonction de numérisation qui ne fonctionnait plus après l’upgrade du système, et pas mal d’autres problèmes que je ne vais pas tous lister.En ce qui me concerne, après une configuration réellement facile avec l’application HP Smart (et non avec un câble USB, qui n’est d’ailleurs pas compris dans le package même si l’imprimante possède bien un port USB), toutes les fonctions sont opérationnelles. D’autres utilisateurs ont eu moins de chance avec cette configuration, alors que d’autres comme moi, n’ont pas rencontré de problèmes à cette étape, qui justement à cause de ces commentaires négatifs, était celle que je redoutais le plus.L’imprimante est compatible AirPrint, ce qui est à mon avis la première chose à vérifier avant de faire votre achat si vous possédez un Mac, un iPhone ou un iPad. Nombre d’imprimantes de toutes marques intègrent cette technologie développée par Apple pour imprimer des documents, sans avoir à télécharger ni installer de pilotes, mais il peut y avoir des exceptions.Dans le cas de cette imprimante il a quand même fallu installer HP Smart pour faire la configuration de base, ce qui permet à la marque de proposer au passage des services payants (ceci explique que le câble USB n’est fonctionnel qu’après avoir tout installé via le Wi-Fi). Après cette configuration vous pouvez tout à fait utiliser les applications natives de vos appareils Apple qui utilisent toutes AirPrint, que ce soit pour numériser ou imprimer.C'est un avis très subjectif, mais je trouve l'imprimante plutôt sobre et jolie. Quant à la qualité de fabrication à ce prix là il ne faut pas s'attendre à de l'or massif, d'ailleurs la première chose que j'ai remarquée, puisque c'est quasiment la première chose à faire, c'est qu'il y a du jeu au niveau de la prise d'alimentation quand on branche le cordon. Autre particularité assez gênante, l'imprimante est quand même assez bruyante.

Review_Title: Magnificent multifunction printer from HP! Good quality-price relation.
Review_Content: The HP DeskJet 4220e multifunction printer is a good product for printing documents, scanning and copying, and in both sections it more than delivers with good quality. It is quite simple to install, with an intuitive process well explained in the instruction manual. We can place the ink cartridges (black and color) before this process or after finishing. I use it wirelessly via WiFi, since we have several computers at home and so it is available to all members, we also have it located in a a convenient place where there is not one of these computers next to it, but to complete the information it can also be connected via USB to a computer. Otherwise, the wireless connectivity is very good and so far it has not caused a single problem. It also has mobile printing capacity, but the print quality will be lower compared to if it is printed from a computer, where it offers up to 1200 x 1200 dpi. The sheets are fed automatically and vertically, and it has a capacity for 35 sheets. It has a reasonable printing speed, in this aspect it is somewhat slower than another somewhat old HP toner printer that I have, but It is logical since this HP DeskJet 4220e has inkjet technology. Even so, it is not an ordeal to print with it. I still have to activate and try the 3 free months of the Instant Ink printing service with HP+, for which 3 months are initially offered for free. This promotion must be activated within one week of starting up the printer. We are not going to be printing documents all day, but at least I will make use of those 3 months and I will evaluate if it is worth it. For those who print a lot, it is undoubtedly a great savings option.✅ In general and for the price it has, it is a very good and effective multifunction printer in each of its sections. I can only recommend it for domestic use or small offices. I hope that my comments and experience of use have been useful and helpful to you 😇

Review_Title: Basic but it does its job.
Review_Content: Hp has always been a benchmark in terms of printers, for my taste it has always been because the cartridges include the print head and even if the cartridges dry out, the printer does not break down as happens with other brands. This here is the new printer basic multifunction model 4220e that includes 3 months of printing. Like almost all of them these days, it connects via Wi-Fi, so you can print from your mobile or scan and save directly to your phone, something that is really convenient. Instant Ink is an HP subscription system that detects when you are going to run out of ink. and they send the cartridges to your home to have them ready for the change.

Review_Name: Jones el Descubridor de los mejores productos
Review_Title: Beautiful design with 🖨️✨ sharp print quality 📄🌈, and endless ink with Instant Ink 💼🏠
Review_Content: This is a HP DeskJet 2820e printer. I was looking for a simple and economical printer, and this one fit the needs of what I was looking for. It is not a printer with many pretensions, it has a compact and aesthetically beautiful design, which integrates without clashing in any work or study space. Its configuration is simple, its interface is quite intuitive. It has connectivity through USB 2.0, Wi-Fi and Bluetooth 4.2. The setup is simple and quick in minutes, we are printing from any mobile device or computer at home. The print quality for being one of HP's low-end models is very correct. It has a resolution of up to 1200 x 1200 dpi for black and white documents and 4800 x 1200 dpi for color prints. Everything I have printed, both images and text, is printed with clarity and sharpness. It has been useful for both documents that I print daily as drafts and also for more important projects that required better resolution. The printer is multifunction and also includes a built-in scanner with a quality comparable to that of the print. The printer comes with the addition of HP Instant Ink, a service that I did not know about and have personally found very interesting. Since, through a subscription system, it guarantees that you never run out of ink, sending cartridges to your home before they run out. However, not everything is perfect, the truth is that I have noticed that the speed of sending documents to the Printer is somewhat slow, although once the printing process begins, the speed is completely acceptable. When purchasing, it must also be taken into account that, despite its compact design, it is necessary to have enough space behind the printer to operate the scanner and change the cartridges comfortably. In short, a very competent printer for Those like me are looking for a multifunction printer for home use or for small offices. It has a very balanced quality-price ratio, and they don't give away 3 months of Instant Ink. I hope you find my comments 📝 useful 👍 and entertaining. Thanks for reading me 😊👌
Aggregation_Flag: Diseño: NuevaNombre de estilo: Sin alimentador automático
Orginal_Review: Se trata de una impresora de la marca HP modelo DeskJet 2820e. Estaba buscando una impresora sencilla y económica, y ésta ajustaba a mis necesidades de lo que estaba buscando.No es una impresora con muchas pretensiones, tiene un diseño compacto y estéticamente bonito, que se integra sin desentonar en cualquier espacio de trabajo o estudio. Su configuración es sencilla, su interfaz es bastante intuitiva. Dispone de conectividad a través de USB 2.0, Wi-Fi y Bluetooth 4.2. La puesta marcha es sencilla y rápida en minutos estamos imprimiendo desde cualquier dispositivo móvil o computadora en el hogar.La calidad de impresión para ser uno de los modelos de gama baja de HP es muy correcta. Tiene una resolución de hasta 1200 x 1200 ppp para documentos en blanco y negro y de 4800 x 1200 ppp para impresiones a color. Todo lo que he impreso tanto imágenes como textos se imprimen con una claridad y nitidez. Me ha valido tanto para documentos que imprimo diariamente como borradores como para también para proyectos más importante que me requería mejor resolución. La impresora es multifunción y también incorpora escáner incorporado con una calidad equiparable a la de la impresión.La impresora viene con el añadido de HP Instant Ink, un servicio que no conocía y personalmente he encontrado muy interesante. Ya que, mediante un sistema de suscripción, te garantiza que nunca te quedes sin tinta, enviando cartuchos a domicilio antes de que se agoten.Sin embargo, no todo es perfecto, la verdad que he notado que la velocidad de envío de documentos a la impresora es algo lenta, aunque una vez que el proceso de impresión comienza, la velocidad es completamente aceptable. A la hora de la compra también hay que tener en cuenta que, a pesar de su diseño compacto, es necesario disponer de espacio suficiente detrás de la impresora para operar el escáner y cambiar los cartuchos con comodidad.En definitiva, una impresora muy competente para quienes como yo buscan una impresora multifunción de uso doméstico o para pequeños despachos. Tiene una relación calidad precio muy equilibrada, y a demás no regalan 3 meses de Instant InkEspero que mis comentarios 📝 os resulten útiles 👍 y entretenidos. Gracias por leerme 😊👌

Review_Content: Without being the best printer on the market, not even the best ink printer, not even the best HP ink printer, this is a fantastic alternative to spend little money and have a very capable printer that can be used with great ease from multitude of different devices.Physically it is very pretty, with shapes that make it look more expensive than it really is, and in the printing process it is reasonably quiet.It is installed easily and quickly. You just have to follow the instructions that come with the product and in a few minutes you can start printing. Big difference with other printers, a Canon that we bought for my parents' house comes to mind and that was a real ordeal when it came to setting it up. This one, in that aspect, has been really simple. And the best thing is that it can be configured so that it is visible from computers, by cable or Wi-Fi, but also from mobile phones, and thus we save ourselves from having to send a file from the mobile phone to the computer just to print it. Quality and speed printing are acceptable, taking into account the price of the product. It should be noted that 6 months of istank are included in the price, a service that notifies you when you are running out of ink and sends you the cartridges you need before you run out. It may be cheaper to look for alternative cartridges once the free subscription ends, but we will have to see.

Review_Content: On this occasion we review this printer that we received at home.✅Contents:The package includes our printer made with 65% recycled plastic, cartridges already installed, but it does not include batteries, everything comes well packaged and protected in a box. cardboard with the manufacturer's brand and its design on the box.✅Design and quality: Our printer comes in a plain white color, made in more than half of recycled plastic, all trays fold for more comfortable transport, it is quite resistant, I hit it when unpacking it and it didn't mark, the print quality is quite good for the price, and it has a silent mode, although it prints a little slower.✅Features:Our printer has a 35-inch automatic document feeder sheets, Manually double-sided printing, Dual-band Wi-Fi with auto reset, Wi-Fi Direct, HP Smart App, High-Speed ​​USB 2.0 and Apple AirPrint✅Operation: It is very easy to use, although it does not have screen controls tactile. Just download the app suggested in the box. You can use it by connecting it to your PC or with Wi-Fi. It also prints directly from your smartphone. The scanner works very well, but only from a PC. The package includes original HP cartridges, and the price includes a 6-month supply of cartridges (50 prints per month). You just have to follow the recommended steps.💶Summary:In short, a good printer for the price, I was surprised by the printing quality despite being a fairly affordable product, to put it down, it comes without batteries included, I give it 5 stars ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐.

Unfortunately, at the end of the process we don't see it in the list of printers, I had to look for it with its IP address. I still find it weird. I recommend this beautiful printer. Review_Title: Features and professional quality at an unbeatable price
Review_Content: It is a fairly complete multifunction printer but basic in terms of finishes and features, which makes it perfect for home users without great usage demands. But from what has been said, it should not be understood that it is a poorly capable printer, since it is on par with the higher ranges in terms of quality of prints or scans. These are differences in speed, tray capacity or manual double-sided jobs. The printer conforms to the seller's images, with a modern design that is easily associated with the brand. Due to its characteristics, it is perfect for domestic environments, so we gave it to our nephew, who from time to time came to see him. We printed class assignments and he is the one who has been testing it and has transmitted his impressions to me. The printer is delivered with user manuals, configuration, power cable, inks and guarantees. In this model we do not have borderless printing available on photographs, although these are very small. Allows the use of paper in various sizes and finishes. The print resolution is 300 dpi, the resolution used in most professional prints. It uses only two ink cartridges, one black and one with the three primary colors, so it is difficult to take full advantage of the 3 color inks. In compensation, HP has tight prices on this type of cartridges. The scanner is a flatbed type with a sheet feeder. It does not automatically scan double-sided. The scanner's optics are capable of scanning up to 1200 dpi at 24 bits, sufficient for most uses. The screen and printer buttons are somewhat brief, but sufficient considering that we have full control from our mobile phone or computer. This equipment integrates into the HP Smart app, allowing printing from anywhere. Installing the printer is extremely simple by following the steps in the application. Its Wifi connectivity allows it to be located without depending on network cables. It is compatible with Windows, macOS, CromeOS, Android and iOS. In the case of Window, macOS, Android and iOS, it is very simple to use. The installation is very simple. I have several HP printers on my account and the aforementioned application, all installed without problem, and in this case my nephew was able to create his account and install it without help. One of the advantages that HP offers is the “Instant Ink” service, with which we receive ink replacements directly at home whenever we need them, at reduced prices. This service is interesting if we print regularly every month. In order to assess its usefulness, we have a 3-month trial (subscription required). As a possible disadvantage compared to other models, we have that it does not recognize third-party inks, or rather it recognizes that they are not original and refuses to print. This is the result of HP's policy of ensuring maximum quality and durability of the printer.
Aggregation_Flag: Diseño: NuevaNombre de estilo: Con alimentador automático
Orginal_Review: Es una impresora multifunción bastante completa pero básica en cuanto a acabados y prestaciones, lo cual la hace perfecta para usuarios domésticos sin grandes exigencias de uso. Pero por lo dicho no hay que entender que se trata de una impresora poco capaz, pues está a la altura de las gamas superiores en cuanto a calidad de las impresiones o escaneos. Se trata de diferencias de velocidad, capacidad de las bandejas o los trabajos a doble cara manuales. La impresora se ajusta a las imágenes del vendedor, con un diseño moderno y fácilmente asociable a la marca.Por sus características, es perfecta para entornos domésticos, por lo que se la regalamos a nuestro sobrino, que de vez en cuando venia a que le imprimiésemos trabajos de clase y él es el que la ha estado probando y me ha transmitido sus impresiones.La impresora se entrega con manuales de uso, configuración, cable de alimentación, tintas y garantías.En este modelo no tenemos disponible la impresión sin bordes en fotografías, aunque estos son muy reducidos. Permite el uso de papel en varios tamaños y acabados. La resolución de impresión es de 300 ppp, resolución utilizada en la mayoría de impresiones profesionales. Utiliza solo dos cartuchos de tinta, uno negro y otro con los tres colores primarios, con lo que difícilmente aprovecharemos las 3 tintas de color totalmente. En compensación, HP tiene unos precios ajustado en este tipo de cartuchos.El escáner es tipo plano con alimentador de hojas. No escanea a doble cara de forma automática. La óptica del escáner es capaz de escanear hasta 1200 ppp a 24 bits, suficiente para la mayoría de usos.La pantalla y los botones de la impresora algo escuetos, pero suficientes teniendo en cuenta que tenemos total control desde el móvil u ordenador.Este equipo se integra en la aplicación de HP Smart, lo que permite impresiones desde cualquier lugar. La instalación de la impresora resulta extremadamente sencillo siguiendo los pasos de la aplicación. Su conectividad Wifi permite ubicarla sin depender de cables de red. Es compatible con Windows, macOS, CromeOS, Android e iOS. En el caso de Window, macOS, Android e iOS, resulta muy simple de utilizar. La instalación es muy sencilla. yo dispongo de varias impresoras HP en mi cuenta y la mencionada aplicación, todas instaladas sin problema, y en este caso mi sobrino pudo crear su cuenta e instalarla sin ayuda.Una de las ventajas que ofrece HP es el servicio “Instant Ink”, con el cual recibimos reemplazos de tinta directamente en casa cada vez que los necesitamos, con unos precios reducidos. Este servicio es interesante si imprimimos de forma regular todos los meses. Para poder valorar su utilidad disponemos de 3 meses de prueba (previa suscripción).Como posible desventaja respecto a otros modelos, tenemos que no reconoce las tintas de terceros, o más bien reconoce que no son originales y se niega a imprimir. Esto es fruto de la política de HP de asegurar la máxima calidad y durabilidad de la impresora.

Review_Content: Once you have got over the nightmare of secret codes to connect the printer to the internet, it is very simple to get started. Diagrams are displayed on the computer screen that you just have to follow step by step. This is the first time I have seen such a well-conducted installation. The printer and photocopier functions are simple. Installing the scanner function was a little more complicated: I had to uninstall the old printer to be able to do it. After this operation everything was simple. On the other hand, and this is the negative point for me, you cannot automatically connect it to another computer. A link is given to do this, the usefulness of which I only understood after the fact and too late. The other debatable point is HP's proposal to supply the ink as you go... I imagine that many users are like me and do not like to be "prisoners" of a system of this kind . Despite everything, I highly recommend this product, hoping that it will give me satisfaction as it currently does for a few years.

Review_Title: Simple and functional printer for everyday life
Review_Content: 💢 It looks very good, and it shows in the details and finishes that we have a consolidated brand like HP behind it. 💢 It is a mid-range product, which performs well for what it costs. Don't expect this printer to give you ultra-high-quality reproductions either, but for basic text documents and graphics, it does a perfect job. But even if you need to print photos, it doesn't disappoint either. The colors are vivid and the images come out quite sharp.💢 Another point in its favor is how compact it is. It doesn't take up half your desk, which is great if your space is limited. And furthermore, its elegant and minimalist design will not clash anywhere you put it.💢 This model is compatible with the HP instant ink program, so, depending on what you print per month, you can configure it to be deliver consumables automatically so you don't run out of ink at the worst of times. Anyway, personally, I'm not too interested because I prefer to decide when I really need a replacement cartridge.✪ CONCLUSION:⭐ A good option to take into account. It is not the most sophisticated on the market, but it does what it promises: printing, scanning and photocopying without complications.💬 I hope this little review has been useful to you. 👀
Aggregation_Flag: Diseño: NuevaNombre de estilo: Con alimentador automático
Orginal_Review: 💢 El aspecto que tiene es muy bueno, y se nota en los detalles y acabados que detrás tenemos a una marca consolidada como HP.💢 Es una producto de gama media, que cumple bien para lo que cuesta. Tampoco esperes que esta impresora te dé reproducciones de altísima calidad, pero para documentos de texto y gráficos básicos, hace un trabajo perfecto. Pero incluso si necesitas imprimir fotografías, tampoco decepciona. Los colores son vivos y las imágenes salen bastante nítidas.💢 Otra punto a favor, es lo compacta que es. No te ocupa medio escritorio, lo que es genial si tu espacio es limitado. Y además, su diseño elegante y minimalista, no desentonará en ningún lugar donde la pongas.💢 Este modelo es compatible con el programa de tinta instantánea de HP, de modo que, en función de lo que imprimas al mes, puedes configurar que se te entreguen consumibles de modo automatizado para así, no quedarte sin tinta en el peor de los momentos. De todos modos, a mi personalmente, no me interesa demasiado pues prefiero decidir yo cuando realmente necesito un cartucho de recambio.✪ CONCLUSIÓN:⭐ Una buena opción a  tener en cuenta. No es la más sofisticada del mercado, pero cumple bien con lo que promete: imprimir, escanear y fotocopiar sin complicaciones.💬 Espero que esta pequeña revisión te haya sido de utilidad. 👀

Review_Content: Setting up Wifi is quite simple, just follow the instructions displayed on the computer screen after downloading the HP application. Thanks to this Wifi, I was able to test and print from an HP computer and from a MacBook and an iMac located in another room and from an iPad. Very satisfying in that regard. On the other hand, the printing speed is rather average, I had an old Canon PIXMA which printed three times as fast, but for non-professional use, it is quite correct. The cartridges are reasonably priced so it is a good buy. Now, to see in the long term. To scan you have to go through the HP application otherwise, by using the Scan button on the printer the book page or other is not only scanned but also directly printed, which is not always useful.

Review_Title: You won't find anything better quality/price, but buy cartridges, which come with very little ink
Review_Content: We have had many printers, and the ones that have always turned out the best have always been the HP ones, so I don't change anymore. This printer model is the cheapest, we can't ask for more, but what I can tell you is that it comes with the ink just to do a test, so order cartridges with it, because they will last 10 days. The printing quality as well as the scanning quality are very good and more than enough for a home, but obviously don't think about printing super nice photos with photographic paper, because this is not for that. Review_Content: I am delighted with my new HP Deskjet 2820e printer. Its compact and versatile design makes it perfect for any space, taking up little space on my desk. It works quite fast for not being a laser printer, the print and color quality is quite good. Taking into account the functions and features it includes, added to its affordable price, I think it is a very good option if we compare it to the rest of the printers. printers currently on the market. It has multiple scanning and printing options that make all my tasks easier thanks to the HP smart application. Very useful for your daily and everyday use. The mobile application is a real advantage, as I can print and scan without having to be near the computer and everything is managed from my mobile. One feature that I love is its smart printing function, which always keeps it up to date and ready at a moment's notice. Also, I'm trying the Instant Ink subscription service, and so far it seems worth it. You pay a monthly subscription depending on the pages you are going to print per month and they give you 3 months free to try it. I would recommend this printer to anyone looking for convenience and quality in an all-in-one device at an affordable price!
Aggregation_Flag: Diseño: NuevaNombre de estilo: Sin alimentador automático
Orginal_Review: Estoy encantado con mi nueva impresora HP Deskjet 2820e. Su diseño compacto y versátil la hace perfecta para cualquier espacio, ocupando poco sitio en mi escritorio. Funciona bastante rápida para no ser una impresora de láser, la calidad de impresión y color es bastante buena.Teniendo en cuenta las funcionilidades y características que engloba, sumado a su precio asequible, creo que es una opción muy acertada si la comparamos el resto de impresoras que hay actualmente en el mercado.Tiene múltiples opciones de escaneo e impresión que facilitan todas mis tareas gracias a la aplicación de HP smart. Muy útil para su uso diario y cotidiano. La aplicación móvil es una verdadera ventaja, ya que puedo imprimir y escanear sin necesidad de estar cerca del ordenador y todo gestionado desde el movil.Una característica que me encanta es su función de impresión inteligente, que la mantiene siempre actualizada y lista para cualquier momento.Además, estoy probando el servioio de suscripción de Instant Ink, y hasta ahora parece que vale la pena. Se paga una suscripción mensual depende de las paginas que vayas a imprimir al mes y te dan 3 meses gratis para probarlo.¡Recomendaría esta impresora a cualquiera que busque conveniencia y calidad en un dispositivo todo-en-uno a un precio asequible!

Review_Content: The printer works very well. In maximum quality and using photographic paper, excellent results are achieved. Nothing to envy of the photographic house on the corner. The cartridges are discounted for 3 months with the purchase of the printer and you additionally add 1 month using this code: 2sqjv9 I have tested it and it works, so enjoy 4 months of ink! Important: during the free months you can print up to 700 sheets per month, even in maximum quality. And they also send the cartridges to your home and there is a recycling service! The truth is, excellent service! As seen in the photos, the printer is compact, measuring the same depth as an A4 sheet. The scanner is very good! And I was also able to connect everything to my home's Wi-Fi, avoiding unnecessary cables. The entire installation process was very intuitive and simple. It is relatively silent when it works, and the speed depends on the desired quality, and can be very fast.

After several days testing the HP Deskjet 2820e printer, I can say that I am very happy with it. I already had good experience with the brand, since my previous printer was from HP and the same range as this one, but from a few years ago. The change has been for much better. The installation is very simple and well guided. There's no way to get lost. I think that any user, regardless of their knowledge, can install it without problem. It has a mobile application, called HP Smart, which is super complete and easy to use. With a super intuitive interface, it allows you to do everything from any device, whether PC, mobile or tablet, thus facilitating all the printing or scanning tasks you may need. The printer has an excellent quality-price ratio, it is very complete and has all the features you could ask for for the value it has. The speed is normal, the print quality is good for a printer of this type and the scanning is also done well. In addition, it weighs little and is not very big, so it is very easy to adapt to any place. Also, it is very pretty, and the different buttons it has are very intuitive. I had not tried the HP Instant Ink service until now, but for the moment, without trying it in these months, I am happy with it. Changing ink makes it much easier for you and you no longer have to worry about running out of ink, running out or buying it, since they send it to your home as soon as they see that you have little left. It is not essential, but it is very comfortable and, for the price, it is well worth it. You can choose between several plans, depending on the number of sheets you print monthly, and its price is very affordable. It allows you to recycle them, too. In short, I am very happy with this printer and its many features. Also, with everything it offers. It is very worth it and I am looking forward to continuing to try it in these months. I recommend it 100%. For a home that prints normally, it will not lack anything.

Tras varios días probando la impresora HP Deskjet 2820e, puedo decir que estoy muy contenta con ella. Ya tenía buena experiencia con la marca, ya que mi anterior impresora era de HP y la misma gama que esta, pero de hace unos años. El cambio ha sido para mucho mejor. La instalación es muy sencilla y bien guiada. No hay pérdida. Creo que cualquier usuario, independientemente de los conocimientos que tenga, puede instalarla sin problema. Tiene una aplicación para el móvil, llamada HP Smart, que es súper completa y fácil de usar. Con una interfaz súper intuitiva, permite hacerlo todo desde cualquier dispositivo, sea PC, móvil o tablet, facilitando así todas las tareas de impresión o escaneo que puedas necesitar. La impresora tiene una relación calidad-precio excelente, es muy completa y tiene todas las características que se le pueden pedir por el valor que tiene. La rapidez es la normal, la calidad de impresión es buena para una impresora de este tipo y el escaneo también lo realiza bien. Además, pesa poco y no es muy grande, por lo que es muy fácil de adaptar a cualquier lugar. También, es muy bonita, y los diferentes botones que tiene son muy intuitivos. El servicio HP Instant Ink no lo había probado hasta ahora, pero por el momento, a falta de probar estos meses, estoy contenta con él. Te facilita mucho el cambio de tinta y ya no tienes que preocuparte más por si te falta, está a punto de acabarse o por comprarla, ya que te la mandan a casa en cuanto ven que te queda poca. No es imprescindible, pero si muy cómodo y, por el precio que tiene, vale mucho la pena. Puedes elegir entre varios planes, según el número de hojas que imprimas mensualmente, y su precio es muy asequible. Te permite reciclarlos, también. En resumen, estoy muy contenta con esta impresora y sus múltiples características. También, con todo lo que ofrece. Merece mucho la pena y tengo muchas ganas de poder seguir probando estos meses. La recomiendo 100%. Para un hogar que imprima lo normal, no le faltará de nada.
